<span id="freeTextContainer1599648604625521776">In short: <br/><br/>First half of the book is 5 star material. Al fucking Capone back from the dead and kicking all sorts of available arse, plus scorching hot and shape-shifting pop-star Jezzibella taking advantage of her...er...appeal on Capone himself and having him do whatever she fancies. God, that was some good shit.<br/><br/>Second half of the book, being a bit slower, deserves 3 stars. Capone &amp; his female partner have a minor role, they work in the background, so to say. The closing chapter...well, that was</span>
  <span id="freeText1599648604625521776" style="display:none">In short: <br /><br />First half of the book is 5 star material. Al fucking Capone back from the dead and kicking all sorts of available arse, plus scorching hot and shape-shifting pop-star Jezzibella taking advantage of her...er...appeal on Capone himself and having him do whatever she fancies. God, that was some good shit.<br /><br />Second half of the book, being a bit slower, deserves 3 stars. Capone &amp; his female partner have a minor role, they work in the background, so to say. The closing chapter...well, that was hard as fuck sci-fi bliss.<br /><br />So, overall, 4 stars is a fair rating, me thinks.</span>
