<div id="review_2627198663" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2627198663" />
    <a title="Servaas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29543121-servaas"><img alt="Servaas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1461264060p2/29543121.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2627198663?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Servaas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Servaas" href="/user/show/29543121-servaas">Servaas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11684633-the-neutronium-alchemist">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2627198663" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10083314573568626925">Another decent novel, however a bit long-winding to my personal taste. I could not get rit of the idea that some character arcs could have been somewhat shorter than they were. The overall plot remains definitely interesting though. <br/><br/>I am probably not going to purchase the last book of the trilogy, however I do think I will check out &quot;A Second Chance at Eden&quot;, the short story collection set in the same universe.</span>
  <span id="freeText10083314573568626925" style="display:none">Another decent novel, however a bit long-winding to my personal taste. I could not get rit of the idea that some character arcs could have been somewhat shorter than they were. The overall plot remains definitely interesting though. <br /><br />I am probably not going to purchase the last book of the trilogy, however I do think I will check out "A Second Chance at Eden", the short story collection set in the same universe.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10083314573568626925" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

