<div id="review_1024140962" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1024140962" />
    <a title="Andrew" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25369629-andrew"><img alt="Andrew" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623180257p2/25369629.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1024140962?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew" href="/user/show/25369629-andrew">Andrew</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330351430" href="/book/show/479561.The_Neutronium_Alchemist">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1024140962" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8756022041300689662">As a novel, <i>The Neutronium Alchemist</i> was not satisfying. Essentially, it is a cliffhanger stretched to one thousand pages, little more than busywork necessary to advance through the trilogy. If I had not come to this series long after it was published--giving me the option to read all three one after the other--I doubt I would have bothered waiting for the third. The investment of time and effort necessary to read this tome pays nothing--it is just a pause between the first and third novels. It </span>
  <span id="freeText8756022041300689662" style="display:none">As a novel, <i>The Neutronium Alchemist</i> was not satisfying. Essentially, it is a cliffhanger stretched to one thousand pages, little more than busywork necessary to advance through the trilogy. If I had not come to this series long after it was published--giving me the option to read all three one after the other--I doubt I would have bothered waiting for the third. The investment of time and effort necessary to read this tome pays nothing--it is just a pause between the first and third novels. It only warrants a second star because it was, generally, written well.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8756022041300689662" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


