    <a title="Damon Smith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5716927-damon-smith"><img alt="Damon Smith" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/499689051?book_show_action=true">Jan 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Damon Smith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Damon Smith" href="/user/show/5716927-damon-smith">Damon Smith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330351430" href="/book/show/479561.The_Neutronium_Alchemist">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer499689051" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8595496068033008520">I really wanted to like this after the fantastic first book, equal parts horror and sci-fi. Yet, this 2nd part was pretty ridiculous. Al Capone coming back from the dead was quite a stupid idea I thought, and the bulk of the book was &quot;run away from possessed, reach new planet, possessed catch up, run away from possessed&quot; etc etc...<br/><br/>And yet, the pure terror of the threat that you felt in the first book is completely nullified in this book, as the humans enter negotiations with the possessed, as so</span>
  <span id="freeText8595496068033008520" style="display:none">I really wanted to like this after the fantastic first book, equal parts horror and sci-fi. Yet, this 2nd part was pretty ridiculous. Al Capone coming back from the dead was quite a stupid idea I thought, and the bulk of the book was "run away from possessed, reach new planet, possessed catch up, run away from possessed" etc etc...<br /><br />And yet, the pure terror of the threat that you felt in the first book is completely nullified in this book, as the humans enter negotiations with the possessed, as some possessed are revealed to be not entirely unsavoury, and even some of the possessed powers are cancelled out by human technology.<br /><br />The only thing keeping me interested is the whole mystery of what the heck actually happens after you die in this world, and why souls are returning.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8595496068033008520" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


